description.plain:
Tyla Yaweh is an up-and-coming artist from Orlando, Florida, at 19 Tyla moved to LA in the early parts of 2015 to pursue his music career. With only a few hundred dollars in his pockets & big dreams of becoming a star he took a leap of faith and pushed forward.

While in LA he experienced the struggles of being a financially strapped artist, he was homeless at one point sleeping in his car & studios whenever he had a chance. Tyla never let his struggles deter him from his dreams, after recording several songs & performing at several shows his music was discovered by Tes Siyoum Manager & Dre London CEO of LondonEnt & manager of worldwide Superstar sensation Post Malone.

Tyla has currently been working on music with G-Eazy, Ty Dolla $ign, French Montana and Ski Mask the Slump God & is currently touring with Post Malone. 2018 looks extremely promising for the Florida-born native as he becomes one of the most anticipated artist to watch out for.

songs.full_title: Tommy Lee by Tyla Yaweh (Ft. Post Malone)
songs.title: Tommy Lee

description.plain:
On “Tommy Lee,” Tyla Yaweh recruits close friend Post Malone. The two sing over a modern hip-hop beat with their melodic flow. They talk about living life with joy without any fears, always keeping hope for the best, and never giving up on life. The song’s title is a reference to the musician Tommy Lee, a famous drummer of the american rock bands, Mötley Crüe and Methods of Mayhem.

Surprisingly, this marks the first collaboration between the two. Tyla has opened for Post’s Runaway Tour from September 2019 to December 2019. This tour was supposed to end in July 2020, but was cut short due to the COVID-19 pandemic, which was going on at the time of this song’s release.
